    "id": "NUTRIENT:INFOODS_VITD",
    "properties": {
      "name": "vitamin D; calculated by summation of ergocalciferol and cholecalciferol",
      "external_code": "VITD",
      "default_unit": "mcg. The value for <VITD> may be expressed in international units instead of the default unit of micrograms. International units are not preferred; however, if they are used, IU must be explicitly stated with the secondary tagname <UNIT/>. Note: It would be confusing and would imply additional information that does not exist if two <VITD> values, i.e., one expressed in mcg and the other expressed in IU, were included for a single food item when one value has simply been calculated from the other using the conversion equation: 1 mcg vitamin D = 40 IU. Consequently, one or the other should be used, but not both.",
